<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>You Learned: Image Metadata</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/learn.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="learn-page">
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="learn-logo">

    <div class="learn-hero">
      <div class="hero-icon">📸</div>
      <h1>Challenge 4 Complete!</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Secrets in a Photo</p>
      <div class="flag-badge"><%= flag %></div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-grid">
      <div class="learn-card skill-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔍</div>
        <h2>Skill Unlocked</h2>
        <h3>EXIF Metadata Analysis</h3>
        <p>Digital photos carry invisible EXIF data — camera model, timestamps, GPS coordinates, and embedded comments. You just extracted hidden info like a real forensic analyst!</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card world-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🌍</div>
        <h2>Real World</h2>
        <h3>Catching Criminals</h3>
        <p>A fugitive was once tracked down because photos he posted online still contained GPS coordinates. Law enforcement uses EXIF data routinely in investigations.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card career-card">
        <div class="card-icon">👩‍💻</div>
        <h2>Career Path</h2>
        <h3>Digital Forensics Analyst</h3>
        <p>Forensic analysts examine electronic evidence for law enforcement and corporations — recovering deleted files, analyzing metadata, and tracing digital footprints.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card key-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔑</div>
        <h2>Key Takeaway</h2>
        <h3>Photos Talk</h3>
        <p>Always strip metadata before sharing photos publicly. Most social media platforms do this automatically, but not all apps do!</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-nav">
      <a href="/" class="nav-btn secondary">← All Challenges</a>
      <% if (hasNext) { %>
      <a href="/challenge/<%= nextNum %>" class="nav-btn primary">Next Challenge →</a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
